# Behaviour preservation (§B7): `then` is recognised as a brancher in standalone mode.
# `then` is a prelude combinator — in standalone mode it appears as Var::Free.
# seed_branch_shapes must provide its BranchShape for narrowing to fire.
# `x` annotated as `number | string`; `number?` narrows it, `then` propagates narrowing.
` { type: "(number | string) → number" }
add-one-if-num(x): x number? then(x + 1, 0)

result: add-one-if-num(99)
